Iranian students are willing to die for their country's nuclear program.
They formed a human shield.
Several hundred university students formed human shields around nuclear installations in Iran.
With his gesture they want to express their support for his country's nuclear programme in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
The students began to pray on Tuesday at noon in front of the facilities and later chanted slogans of death to the United States and Israel.
Several hundred university students formed on Tuesday in the Iranian city of Isfahán human shields around the nuclear technology center where uranium works.
They intend to show that they are willing to defend their country's nuclear programme with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), in a recent report, noted that Iran, according to all indications, is working hard to obtain nuclear weapons.
In Israel, there is talk of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
Students began to pray at noon at the Isfahan nuclear facilities and then launched death slogans against the US and Israel.
