Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner embedded
More than one third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity affects 5 per cent.
Obese children mostly come from families with a lifestyle that is not healthy, as can be seen from current research.
The importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference, is again demonstrated.
At the table, obsessive children are fed, for example, of sausages at least twice as often as children of normal weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had eaten chips the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a chance".
In families of overweight children there is no practice of sports, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and took part in nearly 900 basic education children from across the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program "Obesity is not a chance", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
To date, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th grade.
An adequate diet and sufficient exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obese children.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five daily meals according to the diet: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," reports one of the survey results.
No breakfast but with snack for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, the details, which also count, are also important, such as having a fixed time for family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of school families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of households nothing is breakfasted.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children, the insanity fries are much more frequently consumed.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink sweet refreshments daily (70%).
As a rule, more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed sport, but among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets based on all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal."
Among their favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets.
"It is above all alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments", is reported in the final report of the study.
As main food you take the pasta palm and follow closely the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
"In the control group of the study participants, who filled out the questionnaire after finishing the prevention program "Obesity is not a chance", there was in many cases a major change in favor of the principles of a healthy diet," points out in the results of the study.
Attention is drawn, for example, to sweet refreshments, where many children would start to prefer normal and running water.
Children would also choose more frequently in the questionnaire poultry meat and fish for the main meal and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
