In Need for Speed: The Run competes all over America.
Review
A journey, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of improper neglects of a routine trip during tomorrow's shift.
To some extent it was possible to meet expectations, but this is of no use, if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new delivery, to which the title is added The Run, raised high expectations already before its premiere.
He promised that he would give new air to the old race saga Need for Speed and, as a result of what has been shown, appears as a game that should not end up being a genre of action without more.
We are also curious to know how the inserted scenes would stay, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As is often the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be given for acceptable, but in total computation points are lost due to absurd failures, which have been appearing in the series for years.
In fact, errors cannot be called, but rather, they are the incomprehensible disdain of programmers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasant in sight, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
So it's nothing from the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
Instead, in the mountains you have to be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each race is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, try to advance a number of required rivals (the normal in a classic race), then try to gain time (chronometered classic duel) and then expect a duel against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this sometimes the police appear, which does nothing but make things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than could be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of the previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a big deal, but it can't be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look somewhere else.
But a career designed with a lot of action is worth this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, everything's in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer true of collisions.
From games of this type it is not expected to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrollable pirouettes.
Or even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
Resets are programmed in such a way that when you suffer an accident or leave the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race there are only five repairs available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's nothing more than a help in case something goes wrong, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, even reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, one must enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, although you are the first, fifth or you arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes it especially rabies in situations, when you see that two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or stop.
It's the same when you arrive, because it's programmed because the "surprise" will always happen in front of your noses.
Adversaries also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will arrive at places where, without taking into account the moment, you will always advance the same opponent in the same place.
Also this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come from the front, so at first you can make the car taste bud.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you right away.
And it's a shame, because even if the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and action, so it's often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if merit is taken the idea with fifty exclusive clues or classification in the race so that it doesn't break boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during racing.
You have to be alert to the gas pickers next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will need what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, strong American cars for straight highways and exotic supersports for technical driving, for example, by mountain roads with curves.
Also the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know about the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
When reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending up with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an Autolog function is connected online, comparing your results with those of other players and providing other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race is made in history.
With the car you reach the tunnel of the metro (pass), where you run dark through the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and suddenly from behind you comes the subway convoy and takes you straight ahead.
In the writing we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one even thought a bit or whether the real authors take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most of the pleasant cases, sometimes even superb ones.
It is a pity that, in the most tense moments, image quality is reduced and sometimes in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of their father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game only for their music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game were to avoid absolutely silly mistakes, we would have problems claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
The fun is assured, but prepare yourself because the mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of airport reflectors.
The choirs of Carolina University will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Third World Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival of Academic Festival.
During the same period, twenty choirs from secondary and university centres will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"The Carolina University has a high stake in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the committee of the festival there is the Rector Václav Hampl," said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance for all audiences to the concert of high school choirs, which will be held on 17 March at 2 p.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program is attended by Czech jazz player Karel Rěžička and his Jazz Mass Celebration.
In the evening the concert "Students of Terciopelo" will be held in the places of celebration of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, in which university choirs, including the choir of Uninversity Carolina, will participate.
The objective of the Academic Festival is not only to celebrate the International Student Day and to remember the twenty-second anniversary of the Third World Revolution, but also to present coral music to the public at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
