Brand story:
The innovative IBM begins its second century of existence
If someone sought a term that defined IBM's strategy with great precision, the closest would be "long term".
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and, however, has already passed a hundred years since its foundation.
The basis of this long-term character was placed by the first head of the firm, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He already coined the motto that many problems in the world have a solution if people are willing to think.
His motto "Think!" became his stamp, around which the life of the giant future will be built (it was also the title of an internal magazine that IBM began to publish in 1935).
Watson was also the basis of a carefully raised corporate culture.
