How to detect a lie
A look at the most recent headlines tells us how serious and omnipresent deception and lies are in everyday life.
Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain is busy exchanging accusations of sexual harassment with several women; each party accuses of lying to the other.
Administrators at Pennsylvania State University have been charged with perjury for allegedly concealing reports that a retired football coach was sexually assaulting children.
